snippet.textDisplay: This is facism, but a facism of the courts. We are now no longer ruled by a democratically elected government, which you may dislike or disagree with, but by unelected judges. Disagreeing with the government’s policy not to allow unvaccinated noncitizens to enter the country as not the same as saying that the government should not be allowed to control border policies. The judge ruled that the boarder procedure was handled badly, someone should take the blame for that, but as he still has not fulfilled the clear stated conditions for entry to Australia why should he be allowed into the country? You can argue it is a bad condition but I am not going to go to another country and argue you should let me in because I don’t like your conditions of entry. Exemptions form Tennis Australia, or from a state government, is not the same as meeting the Australian Governments clearly stated conditions.
